JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 228
EP  - 234
VL  - 7
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Although a substantial and growing percentage of the United States labor force, part-time workers have been neglected in organizational research and viewed narrowly in popular and economic literature. Part- and full-time employees appear to differ in at least four important respects, and these relevant variables should be included in comparative studies of these workers. Methodological and policy problems are discussed.
AB  - Although a substantial and growing percentage of the United States labor force, part-time workers have been neglected in organizational research and viewed narrowly in popular and economic literature. Part- and full-time employees appear to differ in at least four important respects, and these relevant variables should be included in comparative studies of these workers. Methodological and policy problems are discussed.
